            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Terms & Conditions: The minimum age for children to participate in ice skating lessons is 5 years old. Children under the age of 5 are not permitted on the ice without adult supervision. We recommend wearing comfortable, warm clothing, including long-sleeved shirts, light jackets, and long pants. Thick socks and gloves are essential, especially for young children. Protection gear rental services are available at the outlet counter. Lockers are available for customer use at the outlet."
